Use|%%key-big camera.full/camera.FREE_MODE|to enable the free camera mode
Use|%%key-big camera.full/camera.FOCUS_MODE|to switch to focus mode
Use|%%key-big camera.full/camera.GAME_MODE|to enable game mode
Use|%%key-big camera.full/camera.GAIA_SCENE_MODE|to enter Gaia scene mode
Use|%%key-big camera.full/camera.SPACECRAFT_MODE|to enter spacecraft mode
%%key-big action.toggle/element.debugmode|displays debug information
Use|%%key-big action.search|to search objects by name
The velocity of the camera is proportional to the distance from the Sun
From the camera pane (|%%key-big action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.camera|) you can set a limit to the camera velocity
%%key-big action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.camera|toggles the cinematic camera mode for a smoother experience
%%key-big action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.camera|disables the cinematic camera mode for a more responsive experience
From the visibility pane (|%%key-big action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.visibility|) you can toggle different types of objects on and off
Press|%%key-big action.pauseresume|to start and stop the time
Press|%%key-big action.dividetime|to slow down the pace of time
Press|%%key-big action.doubletime|to speed up the pace of time
Use|%%key-big action.loadcatalog|to load catalogs in VOTable or CSV at runtime
To show help use|%%key-big action.help
Use|%%key-big action.gotoobject|to immediately move to the current focus object
Show and hide the minimap with|%%key-big action.toggle/gui.minimap.title
%%key-big double-click|on an object to select it
Show the preferences window with|%%key-big action.preferences
You can always go back home with|%%key-big action.home
You can reset the time with|%%key-big action.resettime
Control the visibility of each element from the visibility pane with|%%key-big action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.visibility
%%key-big action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.bookmarks|Create and edit bookmarks with the most interesting objects
Use|%%key-big action.toggle/element.stereomode|to enter stereographic mode
Use|%%key-big action.toggle/element.planetarium|to enter planetarium mode
Use|%%key-big action.toggle/element.360|to enter panorama mode
You can disable all UI with|%%key-big action.toggle/element.cleanmode
Please send us a bug report if the program crashes at|%%link-big gitlab.com/langurmonkey/gaiasky/issues
Check out the project documentation at|%%link-big gaia.ari.uni-heidelberg.de/gaiasky/docs
Big catalogs use a magnitude-space levels-of-detail structure
Try visiting different planets and moons
Game mode |%%key-big camera.full/camera.GAME_MODE| allows WASD movement + mouse look
Try your favourite game controller with Gaia Sky!
You can scale up the UI for HiDPI screens in the interface preferences
Enable or disable post-processing effects in the graphics preferences
Start Gaia Sky with|%%mono-big gaiasky --noscript|to prevent the creation of the scripting server
Start Gaia Sky with|%%mono-big gaiasky -s|to skip the welcome window
%%mono-big gaiasky -h|displays info about all command line arguments
%%mono-big gaiasky -v|shows the version information
Start Gaia Sky with the|%%mono-big -vr|flag to enable the Virtual Reality mode
Create an external view by starting Gaia Sky with the|%%mono-big -e|flag
Launch Gaia Sky in debug mode with|%%mono-big --debug
Download and manage your datasets with the|%%hud-header Dataset manager
Some planets and moons have elevation data and gravity in Game mode
Gaia Sky can use|%%hud-header SAMP|to interoperate with other astronomical software packages like Topcat or Aladin
